        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "perf(plugins): cut plugin-system thrash from TUI cold start",
        "body": "BEFORE\r\n\r\n<img width=\"1116\" height=\"590\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/1fa62be4-55b7-435c-9bb9-002ea3f4124d\" />\r\n\r\nAFTER\r\n\r\n<img width=\"559\" height=\"185\" alt=\"image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/898682ef-04fe-415f-9f65-4a4b2ace4d08\" />\r\n\r\n## Summary\r\n\r\nCuts the plugin-system work that runs during TUI cold start.\r\n\r\n- **Snapshot memo store/lookup keys now match.** Previously the memo computed its lookup key from the persisted index and stored entries under the derived index. Those indexes always differ in volatile fields (`generatedAtMs`, `refreshReason`), so the keys never agreed and every lookup missed. Hit rate goes from 24% → ~98%.\r\n- **`PluginMetadataSnapshot` is plumbed through the provider-resolve and external-auth paths.** Helpers like `resolveEnabledProviderPluginIds`, `resolveOwningPluginIdsForProvider`, `createPluginRegistryIdNormalizer` all have manifestRegistry fast paths; they now reach the snapshot the caller fetched instead of rebuilding the manifest registry per call. `loadPluginManifestRegistryForInstalledIndex` fires drop from 685 → ~10.\r\n- **`installRecords` and `discovery` are added to the relevant option types and threaded through.** `resolvePluginLoadCacheContext`, `buildProvenanceIndex`, and the auto-enable chain (`applyPluginAutoEnable` → `detectPluginAutoEnableCandidates` → `resolvePluginAutoEnableReadiness` → `collectConfiguredChannelIds` → the bundled-channel leaf helpers) now use whatever the caller passed instead of fetching from disk. `loadInstalledPluginIndexInstallRecordsSync` calls drop 291 → ~30.\r\n\r\nLocal TUI cold-start freeze drops from ~32s to ~13–16s. Residual cost is dominated by two single-plugin module loads (Codex 2.76s, Anthropic 746ms) that this PR doesn't touch.\r\n\r\n## Verification\r\n\r\n- `pnpm tsgo --noEmit --project tsconfig.core.json` — clean\r\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/plugins/plugin-metadata-snapshot.memo.test.ts src/plugins/plugin-registry-snapshot.test.ts` — 37/37 pass\r\n- `pnpm build && pnpm openclaw tui` from a cold process — freeze 32s → 13–16s, snapshot memo hit rate 24% → 98%, per-plugin `package.json` reads ~914 → ~370\r\n\r\nNot run: full `pnpm test` / `pnpm check`, sibling-process plugin-install interleaving.\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n\r\nThree `wip(perf-trace):` commits are preserved in history so the audit instrumentation is easy to cherry-pick for future startup work. Their effects are reverted by the chore() commit that follows, so the net diff against main contains zero `perfMark`/`perfSpan` calls.",
